name: Water Wipes
description:
Every day, in every corner of the world, new moms and dads are discovering the benefits of the gentle and safe wipes for their baby’s skin.

Features and Benefits

  • Suitable alternative and cotton wool and water.
  • 99.9% Water and a drop of fruit extract.
  • Suitable for newborns and premature babies.

Guidelines For Use

  • Store your wipes upside down until opening and open one pack at a time. Use within 4 weeks of opening and open one pack at a time.
  • Never cut open the individual pack or transfer wipes to another container as the integrity of the product will be compromised and cause discolouration.
  • Because chemicals are not used to "bind" the liquid to the wipes, the WaterWipes can sometimes migrate to the bottom of the pack making the top wipes feel a little dry. Simply turn the pack over and squeeze a few times to redistribute the water.

Watch a lovely video on the perfect nature of Water Wipes below:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z-p2EMt8J-0
short_description: A baby’s skin is much more delicate than your own. So it should be cleaned with only the gentlest and purest elements possible. WaterWipes are the only wipes made with just water, specially purified and softened, and a tiny drop of grapefruit seed extract. WaterWipes have been carefully designed to be gentle on babies’ sensitive skin. They are the only wipes that contain 99.9% water and a drop of grapefruit seed extract – a natural skin conditioner. Because they are hypoallergenic, WaterWipes don’t irritate the skin and are safe for use on sensitive skin. The National Eczema Association has awarded the Seal of Acceptance to WaterWipes.

name: Kijani Baby Diaper Starter Set - Pink
description:
If you are expecting a newborn soon or you have already had one, consider the Kijani Baby diaper set. This six in one comes with the must-haves when it comes to diapering.

Features and Benefits

  • Comes with a complementary moisturizing body cream for mums.
  • It’s 6 in one and considers the baby’s diaper needs.
  • Environmentally friendly diaper liners made with a 100% bamboo.
  • The Kijani diaper is made of cotton which is soft on the baby’s skin.
  • The deluxe cover and soaker is soft and buttery on the baby’s skin.

The Kijani Diaper Pink Starter Set comes with:

  • A 100% Kijani bamboo disposable diaper liners, 50 liners per roll. Disposable liners are laid on top of the soaker. For wet diapers, liners can be used and rinsed again. For dirty diapers, simply throw out the liner with the solid waste. This leaves the soaker cleaner, making washing easier.
  • Kijani washable diaper-  Deluxe cover and soaker.
  • Two Kijani Washable diapers – Extra standard soaker.
  • Kijani Washable Diapers – Standard cover and soaker.
  • Kijani moisturizing body Body Cream, Lavender and Vanilla: It’s made of shea butter, coconut oil, olive oil, beeswax, Vitamin E, lavender oil and vanilla oil.
  • Kijani Overnight Doubler: Doublers can be used with soakers to provide extra absorbency for overnight use.

name: Kings Kiddie Collection Baby Carrier
description:
The Kings Kiddie Collection Baby Carrier carries babies from birth till they weigh 10 KG.

Washing Instructions

  • Wash with mild detergent on gentle cycle, and hand wash is recommended.
  • Dry on delicate cycle and remove while seam are still damp.Do not use bleach. Do not iron.
  • Please don't leave the product unattended outside. Otherwise, the buckle or other fabric parts may be deteriorated by heat or rain and it may cause accidents while in use.

Cautions

  • Carry capacity: 3.5- 15 kgs (from approximately 4-18 months)
  • Only use the baby carrier when standing, walking or sitting.
  • Before putting the baby in the carrier practice putting the carrier on and taking off to ensure you are familiar with all the procedures.
  • Always check all the buckles and fastenings  are securely closed and the straps correctly fitted and adjusted before using the carrier.
  • Your balance can be detracted negatively from your moves of your child. Please be careful if you bend or lean forward. This baby carrier is not adapted for spotting activities.
  • Take frequent breaks as you and your child may become tired.
